  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accountant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ol><li><p>Preparation of monthly, quarterly management account and year-end financial statements on a tight timeline basis.</p></li><li><p>Monthly product margin, cost & variance analysis and ad-hoc finance projects.</p></li><li><p>Preparation of statutory reports, corporate tax computation & tax schedules;</p></li><li><p>Preparation of quarterly GST submission;</p></li><li><p>Preparation of Journal Voucher; monthly, quarterly and yearly accounts schedule and intercompany reconciliation.</p></li><li><p>Responsible for consolidating full set of business accounts.</p></li><li><p>Liaise with internal & external auditor, respond to queries.</p></li><li><p>Guide, coach and mentor a team of junior accounting staff to ensure quality and timeliness of work.</p></li><li><p>Familiar with cost accounting in a manufacturing environment.</p></li><li><p>Part of the team which is responsible for establishing, reviewing and updating of group accounting policies and procedures in line with changes in business requirements and relevant financial reporting standards.</p></li><li><p>Demonstrates a strong team player mindset and collaborates effectively across departments to support business objectives.</p></li><li><p>Work closely with CFO, Group Finance manager and Controlling team in FP&A and sustainable value-adding projects.</p></li></ol><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ol><li><p>Bachelor Degree in Accounting with certified accounting qualification or in the final stages of obtaining a professional accounting qualification (e.g., ACCA).</p></li><li><p>Finance leadership role with advancement to Group Accountant position for the suitable candidate.</p></li><li><p>Highly proactive, detail-oriented, and capable of managing multiple tasks under tight deadlines.</p></li><li><p>Strong interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to effectively engage with both internal and external stakeholders.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with ERP systems (eg. Epicor) will be advantageous.</p></li><li><p>Practical, hands-on experience for 3-4 years in the manufacturing industry.<br /> </p></li></ol><p><br />\n\n</p>",
